1
00:00:23,540 --> 00:00:28,450
♪Like a flock of birds
pressing ever forward♪

2
00:00:28,980 --> 00:00:33,350
♪Stranded on an island
shrouded in heavy mist♪

3
00:00:34,450 --> 00:00:38,410
♪We may seem small
beneath the vast world♪

4
00:00:38,410 --> 00:00:43,680
♪But not once have we felt despair♪

5
00:00:43,970 --> 00:00:46,770
♪We've crossed waves
a thousand layers deep♪

6
00:00:46,770 --> 00:00:49,530
♪Stepped on reefs hidden in the dark♪

7
00:00:49,530 --> 00:00:54,730
♪Facing sharper winds head-on♪

8
00:00:54,730 --> 00:00:57,660
♪Our wounds now stitched
into battle robes♪

9
00:00:57,660 --> 00:01:00,370
♪The long night
is branded by starlight♪

10
00:01:00,370 --> 00:01:05,440
♪We embrace this deep blue together♪

11
00:01:05,590 --> 00:01:10,620
♪At the edge of the vast unknown,
I remain unchanged♪

12
00:01:11,070 --> 00:01:16,540
♪Holding fast with lonely courage,
roaring without fear♪

13
00:01:16,670 --> 00:01:21,850
♪Determined to be
both my friend and my rival♪

14
00:01:22,140 --> 00:01:27,030
♪No one dares to blindly
urge me to turn back♪

15
00:01:27,030 --> 00:01:32,090
♪I choose what I believe is worth it♪

16
00:01:33,300 --> 00:01:38,340
=Rose and Gun=

17
00:01:38,940 --> 00:01:40,980
=Episode 19=

18
00:01:41,410 --> 00:01:43,570
We've reached the training sea area.

19
00:01:43,800 --> 00:01:45,982
All squad members, assemble at once.

20
00:01:47,930 --> 00:01:49,410
Yi Nanwang, what's wrong?

21
00:01:50,130 --> 00:01:50,690
Move.

22
00:01:52,320 --> 00:01:53,350
Attention!

23
00:01:53,826 --> 00:01:56,004
Helicopter squad,
alternate landing field.

24
00:01:58,050 --> 00:01:59,210
Flight Inspection.

25
00:02:19,570 --> 00:02:20,880
Three-four requests take off.

26
00:02:21,200 --> 00:02:22,200
Timing begins.

27
00:03:23,880 --> 00:03:24,880
Launch the small craft.

28
00:05:11,170 --> 00:05:11,810
Wu Si.

29
00:05:11,810 --> 00:05:12,440
Yes, Sir.

30
00:05:12,440 --> 00:05:13,320
Fall back in.

31
00:05:13,320 --> 00:05:14,050
Yes, Sir.

32
00:05:17,170 --> 00:05:18,400
What happened just now?

33
00:05:21,320 --> 00:05:23,170
What did I hear?

34
00:05:29,520 --> 00:05:30,440
Answer me.

35
00:05:31,440 --> 00:05:32,170
Sir!

36
00:05:32,400 --> 00:05:34,570
I'll continue to develop
targeted training plans.

37
00:05:37,440 --> 00:05:39,280
Targeted for what?

38
00:05:40,226 --> 00:05:42,280
Is the gangway too long,
or is the hatch too low?

39
00:05:42,515 --> 00:05:44,915
Are the waves too strong,
or is the ship too rocky?

40
00:05:45,182 --> 00:05:47,137
Only start the training
after boarding the ship?

41
00:05:47,404 --> 00:05:48,760
What were you doing before this?

42
00:05:49,050 --> 00:05:49,810
Sir.

43
00:05:50,320 --> 00:05:51,810
We have no excuse.

44
00:05:51,848 --> 00:05:53,782
We'll begin additional training
immediately.

45
00:06:03,080 --> 00:06:04,200
Who made that sound just now?

46
00:06:06,760 --> 00:06:07,570
Who was that?

47
00:06:09,960 --> 00:06:10,760
Speak.

48
00:06:13,440 --> 00:06:14,170
Sir!

49
00:06:14,320 --> 00:06:15,050
Step forward.

50
00:06:18,050 --> 00:06:19,080
Apologize, Brigadier.

51
00:06:19,080 --> 00:06:20,050
That was me.

52
00:06:22,320 --> 00:06:23,440
Well done you.

53
00:06:25,440 --> 00:06:27,930
No excuses. You admitted it directly.

54
00:06:28,690 --> 00:06:29,840
Very good.

55
00:06:30,570 --> 00:06:32,050
But I'm disappointed.

56
00:06:33,640 --> 00:06:34,520
Yes,

57
00:06:35,520 --> 00:06:38,400
no mistakes during the training.

58
00:06:38,840 --> 00:06:41,320
It's just seasick.

59
00:06:41,690 --> 00:06:42,960
That's understandable.

60
00:06:43,810 --> 00:06:45,320
But I don't understand.

61
00:06:45,930 --> 00:06:48,640
Because you're a special forces soldier
of the Chinese Navy.

62
00:06:48,930 --> 00:06:50,170
The entire fleet

63
00:06:50,570 --> 00:06:52,570
and every commercial ship
that might face danger

64
00:06:52,570 --> 00:06:53,840
are your responsibility.

65
00:06:54,640 --> 00:06:57,050
One small wave
and you're already seasick?

66
00:06:58,050 --> 00:06:59,050
When real danger comes,

67
00:06:59,050 --> 00:07:00,440
how will you protect others?

68
00:07:01,400 --> 00:07:03,440
How?

69
00:07:05,320 --> 00:07:07,400
I don't care if you're throwing up bile

70
00:07:07,570 --> 00:07:08,810
in your berth.

71
00:07:09,050 --> 00:07:11,280
As long as you hear the assembly call,

72
00:07:11,840 --> 00:07:13,520
you must stand firm

73
00:07:13,640 --> 00:07:14,930
and hold your rifle steady.

74
00:07:14,930 --> 00:07:15,840
Understand?

75
00:07:15,960 --> 00:07:16,760
Yes, Sir.

76
00:07:17,930 --> 00:07:20,170
I don't care whether
you're from the south or the north,

77
00:07:20,760 --> 00:07:22,640
whether you've sailed before,

78
00:07:23,050 --> 00:07:25,050
or if you didn't get enough rest,

79
00:07:25,080 --> 00:07:26,520
or anything else.

80
00:07:26,582 --> 00:07:27,840
I'll only emphasize one thing.

81
00:07:28,960 --> 00:07:30,570
Anyone else might falter,

82
00:07:30,930 --> 00:07:32,080
but not you.

83
00:07:33,050 --> 00:07:34,400
Not any of you.

84
00:07:39,804 --> 00:07:41,071
When you finally feel like

85
00:07:41,115 --> 00:07:42,570
a real special forces soldier,

86
00:07:44,050 --> 00:07:45,810
ask me for your arm badge.

87
00:07:47,570 --> 00:07:48,320
Fall back in.

88
00:07:49,440 --> 00:07:50,080
Yes, Sir.

89
00:08:02,930 --> 00:08:04,320
You requested to keep him.

90
00:08:04,760 --> 00:08:05,930
Train him well.

91
00:08:06,810 --> 00:08:07,570
Yes, Sir.

92
00:08:10,080 --> 00:08:11,280
Listen.

93
00:08:12,570 --> 00:08:13,640
If you're a soldier,

94
00:08:14,400 --> 00:08:16,320
then act like one.

95
00:08:17,520 --> 00:08:19,280
If I hear throwing up

96
00:08:19,280 --> 00:08:20,930
or seasick groans again,

97
00:08:21,880 --> 00:08:23,370
swim back.

98
00:08:47,280 --> 00:08:48,370
I won't say much.

99
00:08:49,248 --> 00:08:50,490
Arrange more training sessions.

100
00:09:02,520 --> 00:09:03,610
Keep your head up.

101
00:09:08,360 --> 00:09:09,730
Do you want your arm badge back?

102
00:09:11,760 --> 00:09:13,250
Yes, Sir!

103
00:09:13,730 --> 00:09:14,880
Me too.

104
00:09:14,970 --> 00:09:16,490
Then act like a warrior.

105
00:09:16,730 --> 00:09:17,680
Understood?

106
00:09:18,400 --> 00:09:19,210
Yes, Sir!

107
00:09:28,760 --> 00:09:30,370
Mom, I'm back.

108
00:09:32,715 --> 00:09:34,130
You came back at the right time.

109
00:09:34,130 --> 00:09:35,760
I just put on a fresh sheet.

110
00:09:35,760 --> 00:09:37,982
Not used to it yet
without Zong Qing around, right?

111
00:09:39,330 --> 00:09:41,010
Look at that pouty face.

112
00:09:41,450 --> 00:09:42,450
Don't worry.

113
00:09:43,250 --> 00:09:44,250
The escort mission

114
00:09:44,250 --> 00:09:46,330
doesn't have a fixed date.

115
00:09:46,382 --> 00:09:48,915
Who knows, he might be back
before you know it. Let's go.

116
00:09:53,250 --> 00:09:54,130
What's wrong?

117
00:09:54,680 --> 00:09:56,130
Acting like a kid again?

118
00:09:58,330 --> 00:09:59,130
Mom,

119
00:10:01,010 --> 00:10:02,450
I'm pregnant.

120
00:10:15,330 --> 00:10:16,880
Don't carry that.

121
00:10:20,450 --> 00:10:21,800
Silly girl.

122
00:10:22,880 --> 00:10:24,450
Let me hug you.

123
00:10:30,920 --> 00:10:31,880
Eat more.

124
00:10:32,560 --> 00:10:34,560
You need good health.

125
00:10:34,760 --> 00:10:36,640
Okay. Don't keep piling food
on her plate.

126
00:10:36,680 --> 00:10:38,760
She just got pregnant.
Let her eat at her own pace.

127
00:10:38,760 --> 00:10:40,440
She doesn't have much
of an appetite now.

128
00:10:40,448 --> 00:10:42,071
That's all the more reason
she needs to eat.

129
00:10:42,093 --> 00:10:43,130
It's also a training.

130
00:10:43,560 --> 00:10:45,330
Eat to stay healthy.

131
00:10:45,471 --> 00:10:47,093
Humans are made of iron.
Food is steel.

132
00:10:47,130 --> 00:10:48,010
Eat up.

133
00:10:48,010 --> 00:10:49,090
Look at your dad.

134
00:10:50,360 --> 00:10:52,240
Ever since he found out
he's going to be a grandpa,

135
00:10:52,248 --> 00:10:53,250
he's all over the moon.

136
00:10:53,680 --> 00:10:55,370
Being a grandpa is great and all,

137
00:10:55,450 --> 00:10:56,250
but

138
00:10:57,010 --> 00:10:58,680
my daughter's health comes first.

139
00:10:59,010 --> 00:11:00,880
Eat more.

140
00:11:00,915 --> 00:11:02,330
All right, Dad, Mom. I'll eat more.

141
00:11:02,330 --> 00:11:03,210
That's right.

142
00:11:03,920 --> 00:11:04,680
Yangyang,

143
00:11:05,450 --> 00:11:07,560
now that you're pregnant,

144
00:11:07,560 --> 00:11:08,640
you're carrying for two.

145
00:11:09,090 --> 00:11:11,450
Be extra careful and slow
in everything you do.

146
00:11:12,330 --> 00:11:14,130
Zong Qing isn't home.

147
00:11:14,250 --> 00:11:16,250
If anything happens, let us know.

148
00:11:17,680 --> 00:11:19,680
Don't worry. I'll be careful.

149
00:11:20,090 --> 00:11:22,370
Zong Qing's away on escort duty.

150
00:11:22,560 --> 00:11:24,010
It's his duty

151
00:11:24,090 --> 00:11:25,560
as a soldier.

152
00:11:25,680 --> 00:11:26,880
As a military spouse,

153
00:11:27,250 --> 00:11:29,010
you have to be prepared for that.

154
00:11:29,010 --> 00:11:30,150
You need to understand that.

155
00:11:31,560 --> 00:11:33,210
Why are you lecturing her again?

156
00:11:34,520 --> 00:11:36,010
It's not like you're any help.

157
00:11:36,560 --> 00:11:37,250
Fine.

158
00:11:37,250 --> 00:11:38,560
I won't say more.

159
00:11:39,130 --> 00:11:40,760
Dad, Mom, don't worry.

160
00:11:41,330 --> 00:11:42,330
I understand.

161
00:11:42,330 --> 00:11:42,920
Look at that.

162
00:11:42,920 --> 00:11:44,210
I know what to do.

163
00:11:44,210 --> 00:11:45,370
Well done.

164
00:11:47,250 --> 00:11:48,210
Let me ask you.

165
00:11:48,640 --> 00:11:50,250
Did you register at the hospital?

166
00:11:50,293 --> 00:11:52,370
Have you made an appointment
for a prenatal checkup?

167
00:11:52,404 --> 00:11:54,071
Don't worry. Everything's been arranged.

168
00:11:54,115 --> 00:11:55,250
Which day?

169
00:11:55,330 --> 00:11:57,450
Let me know. I'll go with you.

170
00:11:58,370 --> 00:11:59,210
Okay.

171
00:12:00,250 --> 00:12:01,560
That's what is important now.

172
00:12:02,250 --> 00:12:03,880
All right, all right.

173
00:12:05,620 --> 00:12:13,580
(Kaqiman Hotel, Roman Islands)

174
00:12:45,730 --> 00:12:46,880
What's the plan?

175
00:12:48,490 --> 00:12:50,520
Check where Atocha is

176
00:12:50,520 --> 00:12:52,160
and plan the route tonight.

177
00:12:52,520 --> 00:12:54,040
I already got it sorted.

178
00:12:54,130 --> 00:12:55,520
It's all in my phone notes.

179
00:12:55,520 --> 00:12:56,730
Use it any time you want.

180
00:12:59,730 --> 00:13:00,370
Good.

181
00:13:00,520 --> 00:13:02,400
Then let's rest for half a day today.

182
00:13:02,400 --> 00:13:03,800
Start work tomorrow at 8 AM sharp.

183
00:13:03,880 --> 00:13:05,160
Got it. I'll put my things away.

184
00:13:05,160 --> 00:13:05,760
Go ahead.

185
00:13:05,810 --> 00:13:07,130
I'll head upstairs and take a look.

186
00:13:07,130 --> 00:13:07,800
Sure.

187
00:13:49,760 --> 00:13:51,450
The conditions here are pretty basic.

188
00:13:52,280 --> 00:13:54,010
Hygiene probably isn't great either.

189
00:13:54,250 --> 00:13:55,010
Mr. Han,

190
00:13:55,182 --> 00:13:57,050
maybe you should go back
to the original hotel.

191
00:13:57,090 --> 00:13:58,330
I'll stay here and watch them.

192
00:13:58,400 --> 00:13:59,010
No need.

193
00:13:59,010 --> 00:14:00,490
No matter where I stay,

194
00:14:00,490 --> 00:14:01,920
I can't show my face.

195
00:14:02,010 --> 00:14:03,010
You'll have to deal with

196
00:14:03,010 --> 00:14:04,400
most things anyway.

197
00:14:04,715 --> 00:14:06,400
I actually think this place is fine.

198
00:14:06,490 --> 00:14:07,850
Clean and quiet.

199
00:14:08,040 --> 00:14:10,210
If Tang Xin can stay here, why can't I?

200
00:14:10,920 --> 00:14:11,850
Put my luggage inside.

201
00:14:31,760 --> 00:14:33,250
Do you know why I brought you up here?

202
00:14:34,800 --> 00:14:36,040
Sir, yes.

203
00:14:38,490 --> 00:14:40,250
This is the highest place on the ship.

204
00:14:40,250 --> 00:14:41,737
The higher it is, the more it rocks.

205
00:14:42,010 --> 00:14:43,490
Everyone gets through this.

206
00:14:47,680 --> 00:14:48,730
I'm sorry, Captain.

207
00:14:49,250 --> 00:14:50,520
I let you down.

208
00:14:56,010 --> 00:14:56,680
Yi Nanwang,

209
00:14:58,090 --> 00:14:59,760
you've never let me down.

210
00:15:00,560 --> 00:15:01,760
I hope you'll never

211
00:15:02,450 --> 00:15:04,010
give up on yourself.

212
00:15:09,640 --> 00:15:10,400
Sir!

213
00:15:10,800 --> 00:15:11,520
Captain,

214
00:15:11,850 --> 00:15:14,250
I'll get our arm badges back.

215
00:15:14,250 --> 00:15:15,730
I know you will.

216
00:15:16,640 --> 00:15:17,760
But do it fast!

217
00:15:29,400 --> 00:15:30,010
Sir.

218
00:15:31,040 --> 00:15:31,760
Captain,

219
00:15:33,040 --> 00:15:34,040
I want to know,

220
00:15:34,560 --> 00:15:37,010
how did you become so strong?

221
00:15:37,730 --> 00:15:38,800
You think I'm strong?

222
00:15:42,210 --> 00:15:43,250
Captain, to me,

223
00:15:43,250 --> 00:15:45,250
you're always the strongest,
the hardest working,

224
00:15:45,400 --> 00:15:46,920
and the most outstanding.

225
00:15:47,250 --> 00:15:48,400
Captain Chen,

226
00:15:48,760 --> 00:15:50,490
Sergeant Cheng, Captain Zong,

227
00:15:50,520 --> 00:15:51,850
and Squad Leader Dai,

228
00:15:52,040 --> 00:15:54,330
each of them is exceptional.

229
00:15:54,490 --> 00:15:55,490
Only me.

230
00:15:55,937 --> 00:15:57,400
I've been holding the team back...

231
00:15:57,400 --> 00:15:58,850
If you were really that bad,

232
00:15:58,850 --> 00:16:00,680
why would I have brought you in?

233
00:16:06,160 --> 00:16:07,560
Everyone started this way.

234
00:16:07,970 --> 00:16:10,010
Seasick, afraid of heights, and fear.

235
00:16:10,280 --> 00:16:11,250
It's normal.

236
00:16:11,250 --> 00:16:12,400
We're human.

237
00:16:15,560 --> 00:16:16,760
We're made of flesh and blood.

238
00:16:17,090 --> 00:16:18,250
We all make mistakes.

239
00:16:25,520 --> 00:16:26,330
When I was a recruit,

240
00:16:26,330 --> 00:16:27,680
my squad leader told me,

241
00:16:29,337 --> 00:16:31,800
"As long as you grit your teeth
and get through the hardest part,

242
00:16:32,210 --> 00:16:33,760
the road ahead gets easier."

243
00:16:35,520 --> 00:16:36,640
Do you understand?

244
00:16:37,490 --> 00:16:38,280
Yes, Sir.

245
00:16:40,330 --> 00:16:41,250
Are you sure?

246
00:16:45,280 --> 00:16:47,160
Don't leave this spot before lights out.

247
00:16:47,210 --> 00:16:48,560
Stand here like a nail.

248
00:16:49,400 --> 00:16:50,250
Yes, Sir.

249
00:17:06,540 --> 00:17:09,860
(Atocha)

250
00:17:13,410 --> 00:17:14,250
Xin,

251
00:17:14,840 --> 00:17:16,730
we've been sitting here for two days.

252
00:17:17,010 --> 00:17:18,650
That door hasn't opened once.

253
00:17:19,080 --> 00:17:20,560
Only the sign says "Atocha".

254
00:17:20,560 --> 00:17:22,250
It's not even a full name.

255
00:17:23,410 --> 00:17:25,280
This doesn't feel like
a real company to me.

256
00:17:26,170 --> 00:17:27,730
Didn't you look into this place?

257
00:17:27,730 --> 00:17:29,160
Are you sure this is the right place?

258
00:17:29,160 --> 00:17:31,040
I'm sure. This is the place.

259
00:17:35,490 --> 00:17:37,170
It doesn't look like a company.

260
00:17:41,071 --> 00:17:43,204
We're already here.
Let's wait a little longer.

261
00:17:49,250 --> 00:17:53,600
One, two, three, four. Speed up.

262
00:17:54,120 --> 00:17:59,600
Six, seven, eight, nine, ten.
Keep going.

263
00:18:01,520 --> 00:18:03,250
Eleven, twelve,

264
00:18:03,690 --> 00:18:05,490
thirteen, fourteen,

265
00:18:05,890 --> 00:18:07,490
fifteen. Walk in a straight line.

266
00:18:09,320 --> 00:18:10,320
Step on the red line.

267
00:18:10,448 --> 00:18:11,200
Walk the red line.

268
00:18:11,204 --> 00:18:12,226
Zong Qing, help him.

269
00:18:12,650 --> 00:18:13,490
Walk the red line.

270
00:18:20,040 --> 00:18:20,840
Red line.

271
00:18:21,170 --> 00:18:22,320
Faster.

272
00:18:24,040 --> 00:18:24,600
Ready.

273
00:18:27,840 --> 00:18:28,410
Go.

274
00:18:29,250 --> 00:18:33,690
One, two, three, four, five,

275
00:18:34,080 --> 00:18:35,840
six, seven. Good. Walk straight.

276
00:18:37,280 --> 00:18:38,360
Quick. Get up.

277
00:18:42,120 --> 00:18:42,890
Straight line.

278
00:18:48,560 --> 00:18:49,320
Keep going.

279
00:18:53,890 --> 00:18:54,560
Ready.

280
00:19:00,080 --> 00:19:01,010
What are you looking at?

281
00:19:02,210 --> 00:19:03,840
Hurry up and eat.

282
00:19:05,080 --> 00:19:07,120
I feel sick. I'm afraid
I'll throw up again.

283
00:19:07,650 --> 00:19:09,010
Training's coming up.

284
00:19:12,600 --> 00:19:13,860
Hurry up and eat. Don't dawdle.

285
00:19:15,800 --> 00:19:17,040
